body:
Draft for now because it depends on #5710

Fixes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/5586

Note that this changes many fused functions from returning 0 to returning -1. I was initially worried about this, but it actually an incompatibility since Cython only assumes `except -1` for non-pxd functions

```
# Nodes.py, line 733ish
                if (return_type.exception_value is not None and (visibility != 'extern' and not in_pxd)):
```

So no assumptions are made about the return type of functions where we can't see the definition. Unfortunately that reduces the scope to fix any performance regressions when using extern fused functions and checking the exception.

commit.message:
Avoid using strings for exception_value of func_type

The main advantage is that we don't end up hugely sensitive to
the exact string representation of a particular number.

Fixes #5709
Shift the exception_value logic into ExprNode
Working for local functions at least
Fix for more complicated fused types
Assume constant result is already calculated

Apply suggestions from code review

Co-authored-by: scoder <stefan_ml@behnel.de>

commit.message:
Avoid "deferred" mechanism

Instead, work out most of the details inside fused-node and
just avoid the coerce_to and type checking stuff for fused return
values.

title: Give fused return types the correct exception value
